    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Medals with Philip II of Spain, ruler of the Netherlands, on one side and on the other two hands clasped through a beggar's pouch. These were worn as a pendants from 1566 by rebellious noblemen to mark membership of their closed group.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
